{"lemma":"سِفْرَيْ","slug":"سِفْرَيْ","root":"س.ف.ر","root_slug":"س-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سِفْر","root":"سفر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19930","n19936","n19937","n19938"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"departure, journey, travel"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"campaign, military expedition"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause to journey, to put on board"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to strip, to remove, to sweep away, to carry off in every direction","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَفَرَ (safara) (form I)","tags":["archaic","form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to unveil, to put away one's shroud","tags":["archaic","intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"وَقَد سَفَرَتْ عَنْ وَجْهِهَا فَتَمَزَّقَتْ","english":"She removed her veil and got torn."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَفَرَ (safara, “to copy, to write”) (form I)","tags":["archaic","form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"written book","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"مَثَلُ الَّذِينَ حُمِّلُوا التَّوْرَاةَ ثُمَّ لَمْ يَحْمِلُوهَا كَمَثَلِ الْحِمَارِ يَحْمِلُ أَسْفَارًا","english":"The example of those who were entrusted with the Torah and then did not take it on is like that of a donkey who carries volumes of books."},{"text":"وَجَدْتُهُ صَبَاحَ ٱلْعِيدِ جَالِسًا عَلَى ٱلْعَرْشِ مُعْتَمَّا بِعِمَامَةٍ هِنْدِيَّةٍ وَافِرَةٍ، طَوِيلَةِ ٱلذُّؤَابَةِ، بَاهِرَةِ ٱلْأَلْوَانِ، وَبِيَدِهِ سِفْرٌ إِنْكِلِيزِيٌّ فِي ٱلْفُطْرِيَّاتِ كَانَ يُتَرْجِمُهُ إِلَى ٱللُّغَةِ ٱلْهِنْدِسْتَانِيَّةِ.","english":"On the feast in the morning I found him sitting on a throne in an opulent Indian turban, long in lappets, brilliant in colours, and in his hand an English book about the natural sciences he translated into Hindustani."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a book of the Bible","tags":["Judaism","archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"سِفْرُ ٱلْمُلُوكِ ٱلْأَوَّلُ","english":"the First Book of Kings"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"trace, mark, writing","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to copy, to scribe, to write","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mark, trace, vestige","tags":["archaic"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Akkadian 𒊭𒉺𒀸 (šapārum, “to send”).\n\nTerminology of the religious sphere, borrowed from Aramaic סִפְרָא (sip̱rā, “writing, book”) / ܣܷܦܪܴܐ (sep̱rā, “writing, book”); compare Biblical Hebrew סֵפֶר (sḗp̄er, “writing, book”). Ultimately from Akkadian 𒅆𒅁𒀸 (šiprum)."},"ipa":["/sa.far/","/saf.fa.ra/","/sa.fa.ra/","/safr/","/sifr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19930","headword_ar":"سَفَرَ","root":"sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saforN","text_ar":"سَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He swept"},{"kind":"text","text":"a house, or chamber, (S, M, A, K,) &c. (M.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swept away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carried off, in every direction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed, took off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stripped off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing from a thing which it covered. (M * A, * K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarati Alr~iyHu","text_ar":"سَفَرَتِ الرِّيحُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~uraAba","text_ar":"التُّرَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwaraqa","text_ar":"الوَرَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind swept away the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leaves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"too them away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carried them off, in every direction."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarat i Alr~iyHu Algayoma","text_ar":"سَفَرَت ِ الرِّيحُ الغَيْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind dispersed the clouds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"removed the clouds"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the face of the sky. (A, * TA.) And you say of a woman,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarato","text_ar":"سَفَرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sufuwrN","text_ar":"سُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She removed"},{"kind":"text","text":"her veil (M, A, Mgh)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano wajohihaA","text_ar":"عَنْ وَجْهِهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from her face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, M:) and [elliptically] (M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she uncovered her face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarotu Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"سَفَرْتُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sfrt Eani Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"سفرت عَنِ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saforN","text_ar":"سَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sufuwrN","text_ar":"سُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"?], signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I uncovered the thing; made it apparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manifest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) [but accord. to Mtr,] the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasofiru wajohahaA","text_ar":"تَسْفِرُ وَجْهَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she uncovers her face"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is of weak authority. (Mgh.) ―         -b3-  Hence, i. e. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarato","text_ar":"سَفَرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ she uncovered her face, ” (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarotu bayona Alqawomi","text_ar":"سَفَرْتُ بَيْنَ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, * Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sifaArapN","text_ar":"سِفَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safaArapN","text_ar":"سَفَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saforN","text_ar":"سَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made peace, effected a reconciliation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adjusted a difference, between the people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;) because he who does so exposes what is in the mind of each party: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I exposed what was in the mind of this and the mind of this in order to make peace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sifaArapN","text_ar":"سِفَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] ―         -b4-  [And likewise, perhaps, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarato","text_ar":"سَفَرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ she uncovered her face, ”]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarati Al$~amosu","text_ar":"سَفَرَتِ الشَّمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saforN","text_ar":"سَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun rose."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-  See also 4, in two places. ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safara","text_ar":"سَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sufuwrN","text_ar":"سُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarN","text_ar":"سَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [the former of which inf. ns. perhaps indicates a radical relation to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarato","text_ar":"سَفَرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a woman, and of the sun, expl. above,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went forth to journey:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) this verb, however, in this sense, [which appears to have been unknown, or not acknowledged, by the authors of the M and K, (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musaAfirN","text_ar":"مُسَافِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)] is obsolete; but its inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarN","text_ar":"سَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a simple subst. (Msb. [See 3, the verb commonly used in this sense.]) ―         -b7-  [Hence, app,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safara $aHomuhu","text_ar":"سَفَرَ شَحْمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His fat went away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b8-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarati AlHarobu","text_ar":"سَفَرَتِ الحَرْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The war declined;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wal~at","text_ar":"وَلَّت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safara AlkitaAba","text_ar":"سَفَرَ الكِتَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saforN","text_ar":"سَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wrote the book,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siforN","text_ar":"سِفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safara AlbaEiyra","text_ar":"سَفَرَ البَعِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarahu biAls~ifaAri","text_ar":"سَفَرَهُ بِالسِّفَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saforN","text_ar":"سَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asfrhu","text_ar":"اسفرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isofaArN","text_ar":"اـِسْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sf~rhu","text_ar":"سفّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasofiyrN","text_ar":"تَسْفِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sifaAr","text_ar":"سِفَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the nose of the camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safara Ailganama","text_ar":"سَفَرَ اِلغَنَمَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sold the best of the sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","K","TA","Mgh","Msb","AZ","Kr"]},{"entry_id":"n19936","headword_ar":"سَفْرٌ","root":"sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musaAfirN","text_ar":"مُسَافِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mark, an impression, a trace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vestige,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avarN","text_ar":"اَثَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sufuwrN","text_ar":"سُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) [Accord. to Freytag, it occurs in the Deewán El-Hudhaleeyeen as meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"track,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trace, of a surge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"torrent."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["TA"]},{"entry_id":"n19937","headword_ar":"سِفْرٌ","root":"sfr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A book,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large, book:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a section of the Book of the Law revealed to Moses:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a book that discovers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reveals, truths:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or a book is thus called because it discovers things, and makes them evident: (M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asofaArN","text_ar":"اَسْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M.) ―         -b2-  With respect to the saying of Aboo-Sakhr El-Hudhalee,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"zlilayolaY bi*aAti Albayoni daArNEarafotuhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        waA^uxoraY bi*aAti Aljayo$i A=yaAtuhaAsiforu"},{"kind":"text","text":"Skr says, [the poet means,] the marks, or traces, thereof had become effaced: [accordingly, the verse may be rendered,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To Leylà there was in Dhát-el-Beyn an abode that I knew, and another in Dhát-el-Jeysh whereof the marks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"traces, are effaced:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] IJ says, [app. holding the meaning to be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the marks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"traces, whereof are"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like those of"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ancient book,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as a portion of the Mosaic Law,] the last word should be from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarotu Albayota","text_ar":"سَفَرْتُ البَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. “ I swept the house, or chamber; ” as though the writing were swept off from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tiros","text_ar":"طِرْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or “ written paper ” or the like, to which the poet seems to compare the site of the abode in Dhát-el-Jeysh]. (M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n19938","headword_ar":"سَفَرٌ","root":"sfr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Journey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of journeying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travelling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaDarN","text_ar":"حَضَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) thus called because of the going and coming in it, like the going and coming of the wind sweeping away fallen leaves: (M:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of going forth to journey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. used as a simple subst.: (Msb:) [therefore] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^sofaArN","text_ar":"اسْفَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, A, Msb, K:) [and therefore it is often used as a n. un.; but, properly speaking, the n. un. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saforapN","text_ar":"سَفْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":":] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnato saforatuhu qariybapF","text_ar":"كَانَتْ سَفْرَتُهُ قَرِيبَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His journey was near"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saforapN","text_ar":"سَفْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to rule, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safaraAtN","text_ar":"سَفَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) In law, [as relating to the obligation of fasting &c.,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going forth with the intention of performing a journey of three days and nights,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness of dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daybreak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness of the day:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaAHN","text_ar":"صَبَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dawn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"morning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forenoon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but app. here used in the first of these senses]: (M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safiyrN","text_ar":"سَفِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sky"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or the former, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of the whiteness of day after sunset."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarFA","text_ar":"سَفَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaAHFA","text_ar":"صَبَاحًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And the prose-rhymer says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA TalaEati","text_ar":"اـِذَا طَلَعَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~iEoraY safarFA lamo tarafiyhaA maTarFA","text_ar":"الشِّعْرَى سَفَرًا لَمْ تَرَفِيهَا مَطَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When Sirius rises in the whiteness of day"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the clear twilight of morning, thou seest not then rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for Sirius rises aurorally, in Arabia, in the middle and the latter half of July, when rain scarcely ever falls there]. (S. [Accord. to the TA, the meaning, app. taken without consideration from one of the foregoing explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safarN","text_ar":"سَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when Sirius rises at nightfall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is during the usual winter-rains.]) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu safarFA","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ سَفَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY safarK","text_ar":"فِى سَفَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodaA@sofiraAri","text_ar":"عِنْدَا@سْفِرَارِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amosi lilguruwbi","text_ar":"الشَّمْسِ لِلغُرُوبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus related, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsfrAr","text_ar":"اسفرار"},{"kind":"text","text":"(not with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him when the sun was becoming white, previously to the setting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiYa safarN","text_ar":"بَقِىَ سَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino nahaArK","text_ar":"مِنْ نَهَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There remained a white gleam of daylight"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","Msb","S","A","TA"]}]}}